    {
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 20},
      "id": 999,
      "options": {
        "content": "## How to populate this dashboard\n\nThe Infinity panels above expect two endpoints on `host.docker.internal:8085`:\n- `/restic-status.json` — `{snapshot_count, last_snapshot_unix_ms, repo_size_bytes, last_run_success}`\n- `/restic-snapshots.json` — array from `restic snapshots --json`\n\n**Wiring path** (planned for backup-runbook completion in Phase 14):\n1. `scripts/backup.sh` post-run hook writes `/var/log/restic-status.json` and `/var/log/restic-snapshots.json` (mode 0644)\n2. Caddy or a small file-server (port 8085) serves `/var/log/restic-*.json` as static files (LAN-only)\n3. Schedule via `launchd` plist `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.iap.backup.plist` at 02:00 daily\n\n**Schedule status:** AppRole + script in place; cron/launchd entry **not yet installed**. Operator runs ad-hoc until automation is wired.\n\n**Until then** these panels will show *(no status file yet)* — that is expected; the noValue mapping makes it explicit rather than blank.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Wiring Path",
      "type": "text"
    }
  ],
